<li id="cite_note-US_Commission_1959-59"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-US_Commission_1959_59-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation web cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=zKIHERHQKBcC&amp;pg=PA379">"The National Conference and the Reports of the State Advisory Committees to the U.S. Commission on Civil Rights"</a>. <a href="/wiki/United_States_Government_Printing_Office" class="mw-redirect" title="United States Government Printing Office">United States Government Printing Office</a>. 1959. pp.&#160;379–380 &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Google_Books" title="Google Books">Google Books</a>. <q>The Mormon interpretation attributes birth into any race other than the [W]hite race as a result of inferior performance in a pre-earth life and teaches that by righteous living, the dark-skinned races may again become '[W]hite and delightsome.' This doctrine is mentioned in passing by way of explaining certain attitudes evident in specific fields of investigation.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=The+National+Conference+and+the+Reports+of+the+State+Advisory+Committees+to+the+U.S.+Commission+on+Civil+Rights&amp;rft.pages=379-380&amp;rft.pub=United+States+Government+Printing+Office&amp;rft.date=1959&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DzKIHERHQKBcC%26pg%3DPA379&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3APremortal+life+%28Latter+Day+Saints%29" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
